tasks.description:
Add one regression test case to the existing `StreamingText` describe block in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/StreamingText.test.tsx` that guards against future library downgrades re-introducing the `remend@1.2.1` truncation bug.

## Background

`remend@1.2.1` silently drops content after inline backtick code containing `[]` (e.g. `` `number[]` ``) when the preprocessor encounters `[` inside a complete code span — it misidentifies it as an incomplete link reference start. The test locks in the expected behavior so any future downgrade to `streamdown@2.3.x` (which bundles the buggy `remend@1.2.1`) causes an immediate, descriptive test failure.

## Existing test file structure

The file at `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/StreamingText.test.tsx` currently has:
- `// @vitest-environment jsdom` directive at line 1
- `vi.mock('streamdown', ...)` that renders `<Streamdown>` as `<div data-testid="streamdown">{children}</div>` — the `children` prop receives the `content` string
- A `describe('StreamingText', ...)` block with 6 existing test cases
- An `afterEach(() => { cleanup(); })` teardown

## New test case to add

Append the following test case **inside** the existing `describe('StreamingText', () => { ... })` block, after the last existing `it(...)` case and before the closing `}):`

```typescript
it('passes TypeScript array type syntax through without truncation', () => {
  // Purpose: Regression guard for the streamdown@2.3.0/remend@1.2.1 bug where `[]`
  // inside inline code spans caused trailing content to be silently dropped during
  // streaming. Verifies the full content string—including array brackets—reaches
  // <Streamdown> unchanged. This test CAN fail if the dependency is downgraded to 2.3.x.
  const content =
    '- **Array literals**: `numbers` is typed as `number[]`\n\nThis paragraph must also render.';
  render(<StreamingText content={content} />);
  expect(screen.getByTestId('streamdown').textContent).toBe(content);
});
```

## How the test works

The existing `vi.mock('streamdown', ...)` at the top of the file renders the `<Streamdown>` component as a plain `<div data-testid="streamdown">{children}</div>`. The `StreamingText` component passes its `content` prop directly as children to `<Streamdown>`. Therefore `screen.getByTestId('streamdown').textContent` equals the exact `content` string received by the mock.

If `remend` truncation were to regress (e.g., by downgrading to `streamdown@2.3.x`), the content reaching `<Streamdown>` would be shorter (truncated at `number[`) and the `toBe(content)` assertion would fail with a clear mismatch.

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] The new test case exists inside the `describe('StreamingText', ...)` block in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/StreamingText.test.tsx`
- [ ] The test uses content string `'- **Array literals**: \`numbers\` is typed as \`number[]\`\n\nThis paragraph must also render.'`
- [ ] The assertion is `expect(screen.getByTestId('streamdown').textContent).toBe(content)`
- [ ] All 7 tests in the describe block (6 existing + 1 new) pass when running `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/__tests__/StreamingText.test.tsx`
- [ ] No existing tests are modified
